<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>Zend\View\Helper\Navigation::findHelper():</p>

<p>$loader-&gt;load($proxy); on line 201 and 204 returns a string and not an instance. Therefore $helper is never instance of AbstractNavigationHelper and loading fails.</p>

<p>Inserting the following as a hack(!) solves the problem:</p>

<p>$helperClass = new \ReflectionClass($helper);
$helper = $helperClass-&gt;newInstance();</p>

